{"questionId": "94ff3e2d", "correctAnswer": ".5", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Substitute x equals 2 into the function", "content": "Replace $x$ with \\$2$ in $h(x) = \\frac{8}{5x+6}$:<br/>$$h(2) = \\frac{8}{5(2)+6}$$"}, {"title": "Simplify the denominator and reduce the fraction", "content": "Evaluate the denominator: $5(2) + 6 = 10 + 6 = 16$<br/>$$h(2) = \\frac{8}{16} = \\frac{1}{2} = 0.5$$"}]}